name: Daylight saving time
summary: Multiple news articles discuss the end of daylight saving time (DST) in the United States. DST, which involves advancing clocks by one hour in the spring and setting them back by one hour in the fall, is ending on November 5, 2023. However, several states have passed legislation to abolish the practice permanently. Arizona and Hawaii currently do not observe DST, and Utah, Kansas, Wyoming, Florida, and Alabama have also voted to eliminate it. The federal Uniform Time Act currently prohibits states from having different permanent time zones, but the Sunshine Protection Act, a bill that would make DST permanent nationwide, is being considered by Congress. The articles also provide details on when clocks should be set back and which states are exempted from the time change.

name: Matt Chapman
summary: The San Francisco Giants have signed third baseman Matt Chapman to a six-year, $151 million contract extension. The deal is a major investment in Chapman, who had a breakout season in 2023 after struggling offensively in 2022. The extension is a sign that the Giants believe in Chapman's ability to be a key part of their team for years to come. Some analysts believe that this move by the Giants is a response to the recent spending spree by the New York Mets, who have signed several high-priced free agents this offseason. Giants' general manager Scott Boras has a reputation for being aggressive in free agency, and this move is seen as a way to show that the Giants are still willing to spend big to improve their team.

summary: The upcoming 33rd season of the popular dance competition show "Dancing with the Stars" has unveiled its celebrity cast, including Anna Delvey, the notorious convicted con artist. Other notable names joining the cast include actress Tori Spelling, former Olympic gymnast Ilona Maher, and reality TV star Phaedra Parks. The season will also feature a new professional dancer, Sasha Farber, who stepped in at the last minute to replace an injured cast member.

name: Georgia shooting
summary: A tragedy unfolded at Apalachee High School in Georgia, where a 14-year-old student opened fire, fatally shooting four individuals. Authorities identified the victims as two 17-year-old girls and two staff members. The suspect, Colt Gray, was apprehended and charged with four counts of felony murder. His father was also arrested on charges related to involuntary manslaughter and child cruelty, as law enforcement revealed they had received prior warnings about Gray's behavior. The incident joins a growing list of mass shootings in the United States this year, raising concerns about gun violence and school safety.
